extend layout

block content

  div.recipe_ingredients
    h1 Cinnamon Swirl Cake
    img(src='/images/cinnamon_swirl_cake.jpg')
    p.serves Serves: #[input(type='number', id='quantity', value='1', min='1', max='10')]
    h3 Ingredients:
    div#cinnamon_swirl_cake
      ul
        li 5/2 cups all-purpose flour
        li 4 tbs cornstarch
        li 3/2 tsp baking powder
        li 1 tsp baking soda
        li 1 tsp salt
        li 2 cups soy milk
        li 2 tsp apple cider vinegar
        li 2/3 cups canola oil
        li 3/2 cups granulated sugar
        li 4 tsp vanilla extract
        li 1/2 tsp almond extract
        li 1/2 cups brown sugar
        li 2 tsp cinnamon
        li 1 cups sifted confectioner's sugar
        li 2 tbs soy milk
        li 1 tsp vanilla extract

    h3 Instructions:
    ol
      li Preheat the oven to 176 degrees Celsis and butter a bundt cake pan.
      li mix the soy milk and apple vinegar together and stir vigorously. Set aside to rest for 15 minutes.
      li Prepare the filling by mixing the brown sugar and cinnamon together.
      li Whisk the dry ingredients together in a large bowl, and the wet ingredients together in a smaller bowl. Combine and mix till batter is just combined.
      li Pour Â½ the batter into the pan. Add the cinnamon sugar filling mixture, poured evenly to cover the batter already in the pan. Now pour the remainder of the batter over the filling layer.
      li Drag a spoon in a circle around the cake, with the spoon placed in the center of the batter. This makes the cinnamon sugar layer curved when the cake bakes.
      li Bake for 55 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

